<centered>
  <h1><span class="pacifico">ember</span> x-editable</h1>
</centered>

<hbox justify="center">
  <hbox xs="10" sm="6">
    Ember-x-editable is an "x-editable like" Ember addon. It does not wrap the actual x-editable library,
    but was inspired by it. It provides much less functionality than the full x-editable. This was created because
    x-editable did not play nicely with Ember.
  </hbox>
</hbox>

<centered>
  <h2>Demo</h2>
</centered>

<hbox justify="center">
  <hbox xs="10" sm="6">
    <hbox xs="12">
      <h2>Text</h2>
    </hbox>

    <hbox xs="12">
      {{#ember-x-editable
        fontFamilyConfig=fontFamilyConfig
        isFieldEditing=isFieldEditing
        validator=textValidator
        value=textValue as |x|
      }}
        {{x.text
          cancelAction=(action 'cancelAction')
          saveAction=(action 'saveAction')
        }}
      {{/ember-x-editable}}
    </hbox>
  </hbox>
</hbox>
<hbox justify="center">
  <hbox xs="10" sm="6">
    <hbox xs="12">
      <h2>Select</h2>
    </hbox>

    <hbox xs="12">
      {{#ember-x-editable
        content=selectContent
        fontFamilyConfig=fontFamilyConfig
        isFieldEditing=isFieldEditing
        validator=selectValidator
        value=selectValue as |x|
      }}
        {{x.select
          cancelAction=(action 'cancelAction')
          saveAction=(action 'saveAction')
        }}
      {{/ember-x-editable}}
    </hbox>
  </hbox>
</hbox>
